-- Wheelock, tycoon raise offer price for Singapore's Hotel Properties
-- 
-- Tue May 13, 2014 10:34PM EDT
-- None



May 14 (Reuters) - A consortium that includes Singapore tycoon Ong Beng Seng and Wheelock Properties (Singapore) Ltd <WPSL.SI> has increased its offer price for a stake in Hotel Properties Ltd to S$4 per share, valuing the company at around S$2.07 billion ($1.65 billion).

The consortium, 68 Holdings Pte Ltd, agreed in April to acquire nearly 214 million shares in Hotel Properties, representing a 41.9 percent stake in the company, at S$3.50 each. [ID:nL3N0N60RF] Hotel Properties said in a statement on Wednesday the consortium had raised its price after buying 17.1 million shares of its shares at S$4.00 each.